  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PA Contribution to Afghanistan (Flood Response) via Sida Hum Partnership Agrmt</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will transfer funds from the Humanitarian Partnership Agreement (HPA), a multiyear partnership between Oxfam GB and the Swedish International Development Cooperation Agency (Sida), to Oxfam Novib for use in a flood response project in Afghanistan.  In response to the devastating March 2019 floods which affected 14 provinces in Afghanistan, Oxfam in Afghanistan is proposing to provide life -saving humanitarian assistance to the most vulnerable, flood affected households in Herat Province, based on the needs and focusing on two districts  Zendajan and Goryan, through access to food, Water Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH) systems, safe and dignified shelter, using a cash based approach. Multi -purpose cash (MPC) interventions will be used to enable families to buy food, Non Food Items (NFIs), repair their shelter or to rent a shelter with adequate latrines, water in safe distance and other basic household emergency needs. Beside hygiene promotion activities will complement the ongoing support.</narrative>
  </description>
